BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 13 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong-sun, 
secretary of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of 
Korea and chairman of the reunification policy committee of the 
Supreme People's Assembly, met and had a friendly talk with a 
Pyongyang-visiting group of former heads of state and government 
and politicians of different countries led by former Costa Rican 
President Rodrigo Carazo Odio when they paid a courtesy call on 
him at the Mansudae Assembly Hall on April 12. 
  The head of the group said he deemed it a great honour to 
visit Korea on the occasion of the auspicious April holiday. 
  Korea's reunification should be solved peacefully in the 
interests of the Korean people, he said, and stressed that all 
the people on the globe should exert efforts for Korea's 
reunification. 

